com.samsung.android.sdk.pen.document

Class SpenObjectBase

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.samsung.android.sdk.pen.document.SpenObjectBase
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    SpenObjectContainer, SpenObjectShapeBase, SpenObjectStroke

    public class SpenObjectBase
extends Object
    Base class of all primitive objects.
    ObjectBase can not be used by itself.
    Since:
    3.0.0

      • setRect

        public void setRect(RectF rect,
                    boolean regionOnly)
        Set the specified rectangle for the region.
        Use this method to resize and move the region. In general, set regionOnly to true to create an object and save its position.
        After adding the object to SpenPageDoc, set regionOnly to false to resize or move the internal data along with the object.
        Parameters:
        rect - The rectangle of region.
        regionOnly - Set to true to not allow the internal data to be changed, set to false to let rectangle change the internal data.
        Since:
        3.0.0

      • setMinSize

        public void setMinSize(float width,
                       float height)
        Set the specified minimum size.
        Even if minimum size is set for the object, the setRect(android.graphics.RectF, boolean) method works.
        This API only affects to object resizing operation by users over object's control.
        It influences the authoring of SpenView. It means object size is not changed by this API
        If width or height is less than OBJECT_MINIMUM_SIZE, the minimum width or height of Object will be OBJECT_MINIMUM_SIZE.
        But, this API can't affect to SpenObjectLine. SpenObjectLine is not a closed shape, so it is difficult to set its minimum size.
        Parameters:
        width - The width.
        height - The height.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - Thrown if width or height is less than 0. If max size is set, thrown if width or height is greater than maximum of width or height.
        Since:
        3.0.0
        See Also:
        OBJECT_MINIMUM_SIZE

      • getMinWidth

      • setMaxSize

        public void setMaxSize(float width,
                       float height)
        Set the specified maximum size.
        Even if maximum size is set for the object, the setRect(android.graphics.RectF, boolean) method works.
        This API only affects to object resizing operation by users over object's control.
        It influences the authoring of SpenView. It means object size is not changed by this API
        Default value is undefined big number.
        If set the maximum size bigger than the size of the PageDoc, maximum size of Object will be twice the size of the PageDoc.
        But, this API can't affect to SpenObjectLine. SpenObjectLine is not a closed shape, so it is difficult to set its maximum size.
        Parameters:
        width - The width
        height - The height
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - Thrown if width is less than the minWidth or height is less than the minHeight.
        Since:
        3.0.0
        See Also:
        getMaxHeight(), getMaxWidth()

      • getMaxWidth

        public float getMaxWidth()
        Get the maximum width.
        Default value is undefined big number.
        Object cannot be bigger than maximum width set by user.
        And if maximum width is set by setMaxSize(float, float) over to page width, it should return 2 times the width of the current page.
        Returns:
        The maximum width.
        Since:
        3.0.0

      • setOutOfViewEnabled

        public void setOutOfViewEnabled(boolean enable)
        Enable or disable moving the object outside SpenView. Default value is true
        If it is true, a part of object can be moved from SpenView area when user move that after select.
        Otherwise, whole object region have to stay in SpenView area. It means user cannot move object to SpenView outside.
        Parameters:
        enable - Set to true to enable moving the object outside SpenView
        Since:
        3.0.0

      • isOutOfViewEnabled

        public void setFlipEnabled(boolean enable)

        Even if false, the object can be flipped by setRect(android.graphics.RectF, boolean)
